claim.claim-text:
1. An apparatus for fabricating a three-dimensional solid object from a liquid photopolymer, said apparatus comprising: 
a reservoir for containing said liquid photopolymer; 
a vertically movable support disposable within said reservoir at least to a depth wherein a layer of said liquid photopolymer contained by said reservoir lies above said support; 
a laser light generator assembly configured to produce light of at least one wavelength suitable for initiating polymerization of said liquid photopolymer in the form of a laser beam directable to a position adjacent said support and focused to a spot exhibiting a generally annular cross-sectional shape having an outer, annular portion of relatively greater power density than an inner, central portion thereof surrounded by said outer, annular portion; and 
a device configured to initiate and control scanning of said spot adjacent said support.

15. An apparatus for fabricating a three-dimensional solid object from a liquid material, said apparatus comprising: 
a reservoir for containing said liquid material; 
a vertically movable support disposable within said reservoir at least to a depth wherein a depth of liquid material contained by said reservoir lies above said support; 
a generator assembly configured to produce electromagnetic radiation of at least one wavelength suitable for initiating curing of said liquid material in the form of a beam directable to a position over said support and focused to a spot exhibiting a generally annular cross-sectional shape having an outer, annular portion of relatively greater power density than an inner, central portion thereof surrounded by said outer, annular portion; and 
a device configured to initiate and control scanning of said spot over said support.
